&gt; surprised me. However, in some new experiments I am doing I am
seeing the
&gt; networks get large (e.g. ~200 nodes). This is happening even when I
make the
&gt; demolishNode probability the same as the addNode probability.
&gt; 
&gt; If you are seeing bloat, how do you combat it? Do you generally have
to set
&gt; the demolishNode prop to be much higher than addNode? Or do you give a
&gt; fitness penalty for larger networks?
